MIDDELBURG - Mineral Resources Minister Mosebenzi Zwane is hosting an imbizo in Middelburg, Mpumalanga to discuss the new Mining Charter.This comes after the Chamber of Mines announced plans to go to court to have the charter declared invalid.Zwane says it will increase black participation in the sector.WATCH: Mining charter's a mess from start to end, says researcherAmong other things, the document stipulates that at board level, half the directors of a mining company must be black.The Chamber of Mines has criticised Zwane, saying he failed to consult properly.Ratings agency Fitch has warned the charter could hinder investment.The imbizo is taking place in a province that boasts large coal mines and coal-fired power stations.eNCA